@node HISTORY "history"

Well what has happened since V1.0?

    · 90% has ben recoded
    · a lot more flexible for YOUR suggestions :)
    · ARexx-interface has ben added.
    · even more stable
    · hotkeys can be changed on the fly

    · and a lot small improvements behind the surface

@endnode



@node description "Wow, what is this? no, really, what is it?"

 @{U}Description@{UU}

 · The Mpega GUI (@{b}TMG@{ub}) is a small, fast and useable GUI for @{" Mpega 3.3+ " link copy}.
 · It features a fast user interface.
 · It's coded in pure C++ and is not another MUI resource munger.
 · Uses BOOPSI for the layout.
 · Coded as a commodity.
 · It's stable :)
 · Can be even smaller
 · Gives you complete control over Mpega
 · Has hotkeys for prev, play, next, stop and hide/popup
 · Hotkeys can be controlled throug tooltypes/configuration
 · Can be controlled through ARexx

@endnode


@node TOOLTYPES "tooltypes"

    @{u}Tooltypes@{uu}

    Well here are the tooltypes that TMG currently understand:

    CX_POPUP    : Should TMG show it's interface at startup?
    CX_POPKEY   : Hide/Popup
    PLAYKEY     : Similar to pressing play in the gui
    STOPKEY     : stop playing
    NEXTKEY     : play next song
    PREVKEY     : what do you think? (8

@endnode


@node AREXX "arexx"

 TMG's arexx-port is named 'TMG_PORT'.

 @{u}ARexx commands@{uu}

  · QUIT
    makes TMG quit - makes no warnings!

  · OPEN    MAIN/S LIST/S CONFIG/S
    open the specified window(s), returns 0 if unsuccesful

  · CLOSE   MAIN/S LIST/S CONFIG/S
    close the specified window(s)

  · SHOW
    acts as if the hotkey for popup has ben pressed, and TMG was hidden

  · HIDE
    hide the TMG interface

  · HIDDEN
    returns ~0 if the interface is hidden from the user

  · PLAY
    play a song based on follwing options:
    @{i}SEEK/K/N@{ui}   : seek number of seconds into song
    @{i}EXTERNAL/K@{ui} : play a song not in the playlist, supply full path
    @{i}PREV/S@{ui}     : play previous song. if random play has ben enabled, play random!
    @{i}NEXT/S@{ui}     : do for next song
    @{i}NUMBER/K/N@{ui} : play a specific number in the list, random takes affect here too
    @{i}FORCE/S@{ui}    : force play command NOT to use random!
    If no options are given it'll act just as if user hitted the play-button

  · STOP
    stop playing!

  · SELECT
    select a song based upon options, random setting has no effect.
    @{i}NUMBER/K/N@{ui} : select specific number in playlist
    @{i}NEXT/S@{ui}     : select next song in playlist
    @{i}PREV/S@{ui}     : do for previous song
    @{i}RANDOM/S@{ui}   : select a random song in playlist

  · MOVEUP
    move selected song up in the playlist. Will fail if no song has ben selected

  · MOVEDOWN
    move selected song down in the playlist. Will fail if no song has ben selected

  · CLEAR
    clear entire playlist, leaving it empty

  · ADDSONG
    add a song to the playlist. supply full pathname

  · REMOVE
    remove currently selected song from playlist

  · SAVELIST
    save the playlist. supply a filename

  · LOADLIST
    merge another playlist with the current one

  · SAVECONFIG
    save the config. if no filename is specified, it'll save under default name

  · LOADCONFIG
    load a config. if no filename is give, load default

  · QUERY
    asks for som setting or attribute in TMG
    @{i}ENTRIES/S@{ui}      : number of songs in playlist. 0=none
    @{i}SELECTED/S@{ui}     : selected songnumber. 0=none
    @{i}LABEL/S@{ui}        : label of selected song
    @{i}SONGNAME/S@{ui}     : full pathname on selected song
    @{i}BACKKEY/S@{ui}      : hotkey for back
    @{i}FORWARDKEY/S@{ui}   : do for forward
    @{i}STOPKEY/S@{ui}      : stop!
    @{i}PLAYKEY/S@{ui}      : play
    @{i}POPKEY/S@{ui}       : hide/popup
    @{i}PLAYLIST/S@{ui}     : should TMG load playlist at startup...
    @{i}PLAYLISTNAME/S@{ui} : ... and under what name?
    @{i}SONGLABEL/S@{ui}    : is the songlabel visible
    @{i}TIMESLIDER/S@{ui}   : can user see the timeslider?
    @{i}REPEAT/S@{ui}       : should TMG repeat the playlist
    @{i}RANDOM/S@{ui}       : is the random setting enabled
    @{i}PRIORITY/S@{ui}     : mpega runs at this  priority
    @{i}MPEGA/S@{ui}        : where is the mpega executable
    @{i}FILEBUFFER/S@{ui}   : filebuffer size in kb
    @{i}AUDIOBUFFER/S@{ui}  : audiobuffer in ms
    @{i}WAITBUFFER/S@{ui}   : wait for audiobuffer to fill
    @{i}AHIMODE/S@{ui}      : selected AHI-mode
    @{i}AHI/S@{ui}          : is AHI enabled
    @{i}MAXFREQ/S@{ui}      : max frequency to decode. 0 if disabled
    @{i}MIXINGFREQ/S@{ui}   : mixing frequency. 0 if disabled
    @{i}STEREO/S@{ui}       : 0=mono, 1=stereo
    @{i}VOLUME/S@{ui}       : volume
    @{i}DIVISION/S@{ui}     : division setting. 0=1, 1=2, 2=4
    @{i}QUALITY/S@{ui}      : qualitysetting. 0=low, 1=medium, 2=high

  · SET
    change a TMG setting
    @{i}PLAYLIST/K/N@{ui}        : load playlist at startup. 0=no, ~0=yes
    @{i}PLAYLISTNAME/K@{ui}      : load this playlist
    @{i}SONGLABEL/K/N@{ui}       : show songlabel. not updated until hide/show. 0=no, ~0=yes
    @{i}TIMESLIDER/K/N@{ui}      : show timeslider. not updated until hide/show. 0=no, ~0=yes
    @{i}REPEAT/K/N@{ui}          : repeat playlist. 0=no, ~0=yes
    @{i}RANDOM/K/N@{ui}          : random play.. 0=no, ~0=yes
    @{i}PRIORITY/K/N@{ui}        : mpega priority
    @{i}MPEGA/K@{ui}             : mpega executable location
    @{i}FILEBUFFER/K/N@{ui}      : size of filebuffer in kb
    @{i}AUDIOBUFFER/K/N@{ui}     : size og audiobuffer in ms
    @{i}WAITBUFFER/K/N@{ui}      : wait for audiobuffer to fill. 0=no, ~0=yes
    @{i}AHIMODE/K/N@{ui}         : AHI-mode
    @{i}AHI/K/N@{ui}             : enable AHI. 0=no, ~0=yes
    @{i}MAXFREQENABLE/K/N@{ui}   : enable maximum decoding frequency. 0=no, ~0=yes
    @{i}MIXINGFREQENABLE,K/N@{ui}: do fo mixing frequency
    @{i}MAXFREQ/K/N@{ui}         : maximum decoding frequency
    @{i}MIXINGFREQ/K/N@{ui}      : mixing frequency. 0=no, ~0=yes
    @{i}STEREO/K/N@{ui}          : stereo=1, mono=0
    @{i}VOLUME/K/N@{ui}          : volume
    @{i}DIVISION/K/N@{ui}        : division. 0...2
    @{i}QUALITY/K/N@{ui}         : quality. 0...2

@endnode


@node requirements "What this bugger requires!"

 @{U}Requirements@{UU}

 · The Mpega executeable.
 · MC68020 or better.
 · AmigaOS 3.0+
 · Very little memory.
 · This program requires the same CPU power as the Mpega executable
   since it's what it uses ;)
 · wizard.library

 · easyrexx.library for the ARexx-interface.

@endnode

@node install "How to install it?"

 @{U}Installation@{UU}

 · The installation is pretty easy.
   Just unpack the archive, copy wizard.library and easyrexx.library to libs:,
   and there you go.

 · First time you start it, you'll have to set the preferences.
   It'll save the config file in it's own dir.

@endnode

@node usage

 @{U}Usage@{UU}

 · Since it's a GUI, it should be pretty easy to use, hopefully.
   But here's a short usage any way.

    _____________________________
   |@{U}·| the mpega gui!         ¬|X@{UU}|
   ||         Filename          ||
   ||-------------------+-------||
   ||                   | timer ||
   ||---+---+---+---+---+---+---||
   ||   |   |   |   |   |   |   ||
   ||   |   |   |   |   |   |   ||
   |`-^-+-^-+-^-+-^-+-^-+-^-+-^-'|
    ¯¯|¯¯¯|¯¯¯|¯¯¯|¯¯¯|¯¯¯|¯¯¯|¯¯
      |   |   |   |   |   |   `---> Open/edit songlist
      |   |   |   |   |   `-------> Information
      |   |   |   |   `-----------> Preferences
      |   |   |   `---------------> Stop
      |   |   `-------------------> Next Song
      |   `-----------------------> Play
      `---------------------------> Previous Song


 @{U}Songlist@{UU}

   **************************************
            laves som main!!!
   **************************************

 @{U}Configuration@{UU}

   · Output & AHI

     · Quality (Low|Medium|High)
       Not much to say here

     · Type    (Mono|Stereo)
       Well, heh, Mono is mono and Stereo is stereo

     · Volume  (0|255)
        0 - 64  is the system volume
       65 - 255 is sound boost and will probably
                not sound very good.

     · Frequency devision
       4 - 11025 khz
       2 - 22050 khz
       1 - 44100 khz

     · Mixing & Max frequency
       Read the MPEGA manual ;)

     · Enable AHI
       Enables AHI and unlocks the 'Select AHI mode' button

     · Select AHI mode
       Pops up a AHI requester, where you can select your
       preferred AHI mode.


   · Buffer

     · Wait for full audio buffer
       Wait's for the audio buffer to be filled up.

     · Audio buffer in ms
       Audio buffer in miliseconds
       ie. 1000 for one second and 10000 for ten seconds

     · File buffer in kb
       File buffer in kilobyte
       How much it should read of the file into memory
       High values gives less diskreading, 64kb is a good value.


   · Hotkeys

     · These are pretty much self-explanetory


   · Misc.

     · Timeslider
       Enables/Disables the slider
     
     · Song label
       Hides/Shows the song name

     · Repeat playlist
       Will loop the songlist

     · Random play
       Will chose a random song to play next

     · Playlist location
       If set TMG will load this file as a playlist during startup.

     · Priority
       Sets the priority of the mpega executable

     · Mpega location
       Sets the location of the mpega executable

@endnode

